\title{On-chip interconnection networks}

\p{The network connecting cores, L2/L3 banks, and memory controllers on a [[JRP0]] chip. The same abstractions that govern off-chip networks (topology, routing, flow control) apply, but the constraints are different: wires are abundant but die area is scarce, latency is dominated by hops rather than propagation, and the network is part of the [[GA7N]] critical path.}

